    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am not sure I follow you. We need to search \"foo\" in fields A,B,C and \"bar\" in fields B,C,D. We must _not_ match \"foo\" in field D and \"bar\" in field A.\n\nHow I understand things is that if you want to be able to have ranked results and correct pagination server side:\n*  you must use only one request\n* to match those fields you need to use the `query` (those are not facets)\n* a single query means a single set of fields to match from.\n\nAm I missing something here?\n",
