  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Surely you can't search for foo and bar in the same interface? the query must be equal if you're going to do a single UI.\n\nHowever what you can do is map the fields to be the same across all record types:\n\n```\n// before\n{ a: 'something' }, { b: 'something' }\n// after\n{ a: 'something', combined: 'something' }, { b: 'something', combined: 'something' }\n```\n\nYou can still use a or b conditionally to display record-specific information, as long as the actual searchable attributes are equal, you can rank them.\n\nIn a lot of cases you can even use the first records, and simply add both a and b in the searchable attributes.\n\nIf I'm missing something, please give real examples of records that should and shouldn't match different queries.",
