    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In the UI, do you have two separate search boxes for this then? or are you relying only on the URL and there's no ui to set these queries?\n\nFor me favorite_foods seems more like a use case for facets than for search. I wonder if you can normalise the values first so they don't have misspellings, before indexing. Then you can use `filters` or `facetFilters` for the `favorite_foods` attribute, and `query` for the full text search.\n\nAre the favorite foods coming from user input? \n\nAlternatively you could also add a rule on the \"matches facet\" for favorite foods and then apply that facet, remove the word from the query, if there's only one input: https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/managing-results/rules/detecting-intent/\n\nIn search there's only one query, because there's only one actual search happening. This is because if you don't share a query, you can't compare the sets of results, and therefore also wouldn't be able to show the most relevant results.\n\nHope this helps, but it may be interesting to contact your solutions engineer for more a more in-depth conversation.",
